ructure meant to impart these ideals - shaped belle époque popular culture is the focus of this book. The author reassesses the meaning of secularization and offers a cultural history of this period by way of an interrogation of several fraught episodes which, although seemingly disconnected, shared an attachment to the potent moral and aesthetic directives of French republicanism: a village’s battle to secularize its schools, a scandalous novel, a vaudeville hit featuring a nude celebrity, and a craze for female boxing. Beginning with the writer and performer Colette (1873–1954) as a point of entry, this re-evaluation of belle époque popular culture probes the startling connections between republican values of labor and physical health on the one hand, and the cultural innovations of the decades preceding World War I on the other.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aEducationxSocial aspectszFrancexHistoryy19th century. 0aEducationxSocial aspectszFrancexHistoryy20th century. 0aPerforming artsxSocial aspectszFrancexHistoryy19th century. 0aPerforming artsxSocial aspectszFrancexHistoryy20th century. 0aPopular culturezFrancexHistoryy19th century. 0aPopular culturezFrancexHistoryy20th century. 0aSecularismzFrancexHistoryy19th century. 0aSecularismzFrancexHistoryy20th century. 0aSex rolezFrancexHistoryy19th century. 0aSex rolezFrancexHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Europe / France.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311099828340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978184545930740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781845459307423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781845459307/original  a978-3-11-099828-3  Berghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_C